## What I Worked On Today

The control implementation plan draws from the SSP v1.2, the SAR findings, the continuous monitoring record, and the Day 89 risk register. The organizing principle is risk-based: for each significant risk in the register, which controls address it, what is the current implementation status of those controls, and what is the residual gap between implementation and effectiveness?

I also address the policy architecture — which policies currently exist in documented form, which exist only as SSP references, and which are second-year development priorities.

