## What Actually Clicked for Me

The insight that clarified the control implementation section today is understanding that control implementation and control effectiveness are different things, and that a security program can have excellent implementation documentation alongside genuine effectiveness gaps.

The OpenMRS program has both. The formal assessment produced SAR findings that documented control implementation as largely compliant — the controls are configured and operational. Eight months of monitoring have produced findings that reveal effectiveness gaps: M-002 showed that CM-3 was implemented but not consistently followed; the AU-12 self-assessment finding showed that AU-12 was implemented but not capturing the full required event set; the M-004 finding showed that AC-2 was implemented but the HR notification process did not reliably trigger ISSO action on role changes.

These effectiveness gaps are not failures of the security program — they are the continuous monitoring program working as designed. The Day 70 assessment framework described the distinction between present controls and effective controls. The capstone control section is where that distinction is documented comprehensively.

