### RS-003: S3 Misconfiguration (LOW-MODERATE)

**Primary controls addressing this risk:**

*SC-28 (Protection of Information at Rest):* S3 server-side encryption with AES-256 and customer-managed KMS key. Implementation status: COMPLIANT; Config rule continuously monitoring. Current state: effective.

*AC-3 (Access Enforcement) / AC-6 (Least Privilege):* S3 Block Public Access enabled at bucket and account level. Bucket policy restricts access to authorized IAM roles only. Implementation status: COMPLIANT; Config rules `s3-bucket-level-public-access-prohibition` and `s3-account-level-public-access-blocks` continuously monitoring. Current state: effective — defense-in-depth (bucket-level + account-level Block Public Access) means two independent misconfigurations would be required to expose bucket contents.

*CM-3 (Configuration Change Control):* S3 configuration changes should follow CM-3 process. Effectiveness note: M-002 pattern (IAM changes outside CM-3) demonstrates the IT Administrator will occasionally make changes without ISSO notification; EventBridge alert for S3 configuration changes would catch post-hoc any unauthorized change.

**Control coverage assessment for RS-003:** Multiple overlapping controls (encryption, Block Public Access at two levels, Config monitoring) make this the most technically well-controlled risk in the register. The risk rating reduction from initial Moderate to current LOW-MODERATE is justified by the defense-in-depth architecture.

